bbc news looks know don't know earth's changing climate. planet's climate constantly changing geological time. global average temperature today 15c, though geological evidence suggests much higher lower past. however, current period warming occurring rapidly many past events. scientists concerned natural fluctuation, variability, overtaken rapid human-induced warming serious implications stability planet's climate. greenhouse effect refers way earth's atmosphere traps energy sun. solar energy radiating back space earth's surface absorbed atmospheric greenhouse gases re-emitted directions. energy radiates back planet heats lower atmosphere surface. without effect, earth would 30c colder, making planet hostile life. scientists believe adding natural greenhouse effect gases released industry agriculture (known emissions), trapping energy increasing temperature. commonly referred global warming climate change. important greenhouse gases terms contribution warming water vapour, concentrations show little change persists atmosphere days. hand, carbon dioxide (co2) persists much longer (it would take hundreds years return pre-industrial levels). addition, much co2 soaked natural reservoirs oceans. man-made emissions co2 burning fossil fuels, well cutting carbon-absorbing forests. greenhouse gases methane nitrous oxide also released human activities, overall abundance small compared carbon dioxide. since industrial revolution began 1750, co2 levels risen 30% methane levels risen 140%. concentration co2 atmosphere higher time least 800,000 years. temperature records going back late 19th century show average temperature earth's surface increased 0.8c (1.4f) last 100 years. 0.6c (1.0f) warming occurred last three decades. satellite data shows average increase global sea levels 3mm per year recent decades. large proportion change sea level accounted thermal expansion seawater. seawater warms up, molecules become less densely packed, causing increase volume ocean. melting mountain glaciers retreat polar ice sheets also important contributors. glaciers temperate regions world along antarctic peninsula retreat. since 1979, satellite records show dramatic decline arctic sea-ice extent, annual rate 4% per decade. 2012, ice extent reached record minimum 50% lower 1979-2000 average. greenland ice sheet experienced record melting recent years; entire 2.8 million cu km sheet melt, would raise sea levels 6m. satellite data shows west antarctic ice sheet also losing mass, recent study indicated east antarctica, displayed clear warming cooling trend, may also started lose mass last years. scientists expecting dramatic changes. places, mass may actually increase warming temperatures drive production snows. effects changing climate also seen vegetation land animals. include earlier flowering fruiting times plants changes territories (or ranges) occupied animals. last years, lot talk pause global warming. commentators argued since 1998, significant global warming despite ever increasing amounts carbon dioxide emitted. scientists tried explain number ways. include: general consensus precise mechanism behind pause. would seem hiatus come abrupt halt: years 2014, 2015 2016 three hottest years record. fact, study published science journal june 2015 doubted warming hiatus first place. 2013 assessment, intergovernmental panel climate change (ipcc) forecast range possible scenarios based computer modelling. simulations indicate global surface temperature change end 21st century likely exceed 1.5c, relative 1850. threshold 2c generally regarded gateway dangerous warming. even cut greenhouse gas emissions dramatically now, scientists say effects continue parts climate system, particularly large bodies water ice, take hundreds years respond changes temperature. also takes greenhouse gases decades removed atmosphere. scale potential impacts uncertain. changes could drive freshwater shortages, bring sweeping changes food production conditions, increase number deaths floods, storms, heat waves droughts. climate change expected increase frequency extreme weather events - though linking single event global warming complicated. scientists forecast rainfall overall, say risk drought inland areas hot summers increase. flooding expected storms rising sea levels. are, however, likely strong regional variations patterns. poorer countries, least equipped deal rapid change, could suffer most. plant animal extinctions predicted habitats change faster species adapt, world health organization (who) warned health millions could threatened increases malaria, water-borne disease malnutrition. increased amount co2 released atmosphere, increased uptake co2 oceans, leads becoming acidic. ongoing process acidification could pose major problems world's coral reefs, changes chemistry prevent corals forming calcified skeleton, essential survival. computer models used study dynamics earth's climate make projections future temperature change. climate models differ "climate sensitivity" - amount warming cooling occurs particular factor, co2. goes down. models also differ way express "climate feedbacks". global warming cause changes look likely create heating, release large quantities greenhouse gas methane permafrost (permanently frozen soil found mainly arctic) melts. known positive climate feedback. negative feedbacks exist could offset warming. various "reservoirs" earth absorb co2 part carbon cycle - process carbon exchanged between, example, oceans land. question is: balance out? more: bbc news climate change special report
پاکستانی کرکٹ ٹیم کے آف سپنر محمد حفیظ کے بولنگ ایکشن کا بائیو مکنیک ٹیسٹ یکم نومبر کو انگلینڈ کی لفبرا یونیورسٹی میں ہو گا۔ محمد حفیظ تیس اکتوبر کو انگلینڈ روانہ ہوں گے۔ یاد رہے کہ محمد حفیظ کے بولنگ ایکشن کے مشکوک ہونے کے بارے میں پاکستان اور سری لنکا کے درمیان ابوظہبی میں کھیلے گئے تیسرے ون ڈے انٹرنیشنل کے امپائرز نے رپورٹ کی تھی۔ محمد حفیظ کا بولنگ ایکشن ایک بار پھر مشکوک قرار نوجوان ٹیم کا بڑا کارنامہ اگلے ورلڈ کپ کی ٹرافی بھی بعید نہیں ہے پاکستان کا نو سال بعد ون ڈے سیریز میں کلین سویپ نامہ نگار عبدالرشید شکور کے مطابق آئی سی سی کے قواعد وضوابط کے مطابق محمد حفیظ کو اپنے بولنگ ایکشن کی درستگی کے لیے 14 روز دیے گئے ہیں۔ محمد حفیظ اس سے قبل دسمبر 2014 میں مشکوک بولنگ ایکشن کی زد میں آئے تھے اور بولنگ ایکشن کی درستگی کے بعد انہیں اپریل 2015 میں دوبارہ بولنگ کی اجازت مل گئی تھی۔ لیکن اسی سال جون میں پاکستان اور سری لنکا کے درمیان گال میں کھیلے گئے ٹیسٹ کے امپائرز نے ان کے بولنگ ایکشن کے بارے میں دوبارہ رپورٹ دی تھی چونکہ وہ ایک سال کے عرصے میں دوبارہ مشکوک بولنگ ایکشن کی زد میں آئے لہٰذا قوانین کے تحت ان پر ایک سال کے لیے بولنگ کرنے پر پابندی عائد کر دی گئی تھی۔ نومبر 2016 میں محمد حفیظ نے نیشنل کرکٹ سینٹر برسبین میں اپنا بائیو مکینک ٹیسٹ دیا تھا جس کی رپورٹ کی روشنی میں وہ دوبارہ بولنگ کے اہل قرار دے دیے گئے تھے۔
