giselle cycowicz (born friedman) remembers father, wolf, warm, kind religious man. "he scholar," says, "he always book open, studying talmud [compendium jewish law], also businessman looked family." war, friedmans lived happy, comfortable life khust, czechoslovak town large jewish population fringes hungary. changed 1939, pro-nazi hungarian troops, later nazi germany, invaded, town's jews deported auschwitz. giselle last saw father, "strong healthy", hours family arrived birkenau section death camp. wolf selected workforce fellow prisoner orders would let go him. "that would chance maybe kiss last time," giselle, 89, says, voice cracking emotion. giselle, mother sister survived, somehow, five months "the hell" auschwitz. later learned october 1944 "a skeletal man" passed women's camp relayed message anyone alive khust. "tell 200 men brought back coal mine. tell tomorrow won't anymore." man wolf friedman. gassed next day. six million jews murdered nazis accomplices world war two. many cases entire towns' jewish populations wiped out, survivors bear witness - part nazis' plan total annihilation european jewry. since 1954, israel's holocaust memorial, yad vashem ("a memorial name"), working recover names victims, date managed identify 4.7 million. "every name important us," says dr alexander avram, director yad vashem's hall names central database shoah [holocaust] victims' names. "every new name add database victory nazis, intent nazis wipe jewish people. every new name small victory oblivion." institution, sprawling complex buildings, trees gardens western slopes mount herzl, gathers details victims two ways: information knowledge deceased, archive sources, ranging nazi deportation lists jewish school yearbooks. today giselle come dedicate father's name, nearly 73 years killed, small piece vast jigsaw. helped trained staff process recording wolf's details page testimony, one-page form documenting biographical information deceased, lived war, occupation members family