spice saffron, well famously expensive, packed antioxidants. said help combat depression lower blood pressure, soften skin hair essential broad range dishes swedish buns paella. what's stopping becoming fashionable turmeric cinnamon? high price? palm five tiny strands, like pieces slightly fraying dark red sewing thread, smell rather like fruity tobacco. four i'm placing cup dousing warm water; they're destined cooking pot. fifth place tongue. i'm told taste test essential check i'm using proper saffron. all, you've spent £5 gram anything, want sure it's real thing. seconds i'm gratified that, despite languished back spice cupboard quite time, tiny threads still capable imparting heady floral aroma, honey notes, slight astringency i've promised. strands water leaching orangey hue, should. saffron central national cuisines morocco himalayas, essential dishes risotto milanese kashmiri curry. well sought-after culinary ingredient versatile spice also increasingly added medications cosmetics. cleopatra used infuse bathwater. alexander great bathed battle wounds drank saffron tea. 14th century used combat bubonic plague key ingredient dishes spanish paella, persian rice dishes indian curries added products coffee salt, skin creams shampoos. saffron used traditional medicine treat menstrual problems, depression, asthma sexual dysfunction trialled research conditions memory loss cancer, evidence far inconclusive yet reputation spice, dubbed "red gold", still glister quite brightly perhaps should. keith alaniz, american soldier-turned-entrepreneur, thinks understands why. serving afghanistan, two veterans decided establish social enterprise based crop could offer locals better returns illegal opium poppy cultivation. company, rumi spice, buys saffron crocuses local growers employs 380 afghan women painstaking work separating tiny rust-red stigmas centre crocus petals, stamens rest flower head, prior dried packed export. it's long laborious hours work makes saffron expensive