tradition going back several centuries. one many countries new zealand germany, greece india, producers recognising potential high-grade saffron, transparent country origin quality labelling, reassure consumers worth high price tag. iran supplies around 90% world's saffron, signs traceability certification becoming priorities. "we trying show quality iranian saffron people world," says mehrdad rowhani, chief executive family-owned wholesaler mashhad, city heart iran's saffron growing region. years hampered american sanctions, meant lot iranian saffron ended exported bulk repackaged sold "produce spain" sold via backdoor bartering deals, iranian producers able sell directly western customers. could impact anything else standard saffron available ordinary shoppers, iran's producers embrace opportunity emphasise authenticity, origin quality product. mr rowhani says firm's exports already doubled since sanctions lifted. "we started exporting united states good - big - customers there," says. he's focusing improving every step production process planting, harvesting drying, selling smaller, better designed packaging. "when see persian saffron high quality, want buy more," adds.
