abu anis realised something unusual happening heard sound explosions coming old city western bank tigris runs mosul. "i phoned friends there, said armed groups taken over, foreign, iraqis," computer technician said. "the gunmen told them, 'we've come get rid iraqi army, help you.'" following day, attackers crossed river took half city. iraqi army police, vastly outnumbered assailants, broke fled, officers first, many soldiers stripping uniforms joined flood panicked civilians. 10 june 2014, iraq's second biggest city, population around two million, fallen militants group calling islamic state iraq al-sham/the levant (isis isil). four days earlier, black banners streaming, hundred sunni militants crossed desert border cavalcade bases eastern syria met little resistance moved towards biggest prize. rich dividends immediate. iraqi army, rebuilt, trained equipped americans since us-led invasion 2003, abandoned large quantities armoured vehicles advanced weaponry, eagerly seized militants. also reportedly grabbed something like $500m central bank's mosul branch. "at beginning, behaved well," said abu anis. "they took barricades army put quarters. people liked that. checkpoints friendly helpful - 'anything need, we're you.'" mosul honeymoon last weeks. road, terrible things already happening. iraqi army collapsed throughout north, militants moved swiftly tigris river valley. towns villages fell like skittles. within day captured town baiji huge oil refinery, moved swiftly seize saddam hussein's old hometown, tikrit, sunni hotbed. outside tikrit big military base, taken americans 2003 renamed camp speicher first us casualty 1991 "desert storm" gulf war iraq, pilot called scott speicher, shot al-anbar province west. camp speicher, full iraqi military recruits, surrounded isis militants surrendered. thousands captives sorted, shia weeded out, bound, trucked away systematically shot dead prepared trenches. around 1,700 believed massacred cold blood. mass graves still exhumed. far trying cover atrocity, isis revelled it, posting internet videos pictures showing shia prisoners taken away shot black-clad militants. terms exultant cruelty brutality, worse long coming. pause two months, isis - rebranded "islamic state" (is) - erupted again, taking large areas northern iraq controlled kurds. included town sinjar, mainly populated yazidis, ancient religious minority regarded heretics. hundreds yazidi men failed escape simply killed. women children separated taken away war booty, sold bartered chattels, used sex slaves. thousands still missing, enduring fate. deliberately shocking, bloodthirsty exhibitionism reached climax towards end month, august 2014. issued video showing notorious, london-accented late executioner mohammed emwazi (sardonically nicknamed "jihadi john" former captives) gruesomely beheading american journalist james foley. following weeks, american british journalists aid workers - steven sotloff, david haines, alan henning, peter kassig (who converted islam changed name abdul rahman) - appeared slaughtered similar, slickly produced videos, replete propaganda statements dire warnings. space months, blasted way obscurity centre world stage. almost overnight, became household word. seven-and-a-half thousand miles (12,000km) away, australian prime minister tony abbott summed breathtaking novelty horror. was, said "medieval barbarism, perpetrated spread modern technology". arrived, world taking notice. men black appear blue. long time coming. theology murder ideological religious roots like-minded groups go deep history, almost beginning islam 7th century ad. like christianity six centuries it, judaism eight centuries that, islam born harsh, tribal world middle east. "the original texts, old testament koran, reflected primitive tribal jewish arab societies, codes set forth severe," writes historian author william polk. "they aimed, old testament, preserving enhancing tribal cohesion power and, koran, destroying vestiges pagan belief practice. neither early judaism islam allowed deviation. authoritarian theocracies." history moved on, islam spread vast region, encountering adjusting numerous societies, faiths cultures. inevitably practice mutated different ways, often becoming pragmatic indulgent, often given second place demands power politics temporal rulers. hardline muslim traditionalists amounted deviationism, early on, clash ideas arguing strict return "purity" early days islam often paid price. eminent scholar ahmad ibn hanbal (780-855), founded one main schools sunni islamic jurisprudence, jailed flogged unconscious dispute abbasid caliph baghdad. nearly five centuries later, another supreme theologian strict orthodox school, ibn taymiyya, died prison damascus. two men seen spiritual forefathers later thinkers movements became known "salafist", advocating return ways first muslim ancestors, salaf al-salih (righteous ancestors). inspired later figure whose thinking writings huge continuing impact region salafist movement, one form which, wahhabism, took name. muhammad ibn abd al-wahhab born 1703 small village nejd region middle arabian peninsula. devout islamic scholar, espoused developed puritanical strict version saw original faith, sought spread entering pacts holders political military power. early foray direction, first action destroy tomb zayd ibn al-khattab, one companions prophet muhammad, grounds austere doctrine salafist theology, veneration tombs constitutes shirk, revering something someone allah. 1744 abd al-wahhab made crucial alliance local ruler, muhammad ibn saud. pact whereby wahhabism provided spiritual ideological dimension saudi political military expansion, benefit both. passing several mutations, dual alliance took peninsula endured day, house saud ruling sometimes uneasy concert ultra-conservative wahhabi religious establishment. entrenchment wahhabi salafism saudi arabia - billions petrodollars gained access - provided one wellsprings jihadist militancy region modern times. jihad means struggle path allah, mean many kinds personal struggle, often taken mean waging holy war. man widely credited, blamed, bringing salafism 20th century egyptian thinker sayyid qutb. provided direct bridge thought heritage abd al-wahhab predecessors new generation jihadist militants, leading al-qaeda follow. born small village upper egypt 1906, sayyid qutb found odds way islam taught managed around him. far converting ways west, two-year study period us late 1940s left disgusted judged unbridled godless materialism debauchery, fundamentalist islamic outlook honed harder. back egypt, developed view west imposing control directly indirectly region wake ottoman empire's collapse world war one, collaboration local rulers might claim muslims, fact deviated far right path longer considered such. qutb, offensive jihad west local agents way muslim world redeem itself. essence, kind takfir - branding another muslim apostate kafir (infidel), making justified even obligatory meritorious kill him. although theorist intellectual rather active jihadist, qutb judged dangerously subversive egyptian authorities. hanged 1966 charges involvement muslim brotherhood plot assassinate nationalist president, gamal abdel nasser. qutb time, ideas lived 24 books wrote, read tens millions, personal contact circles people like ayman al-zawahiri, another egyptian current al-qaeda leader. another intimate al-qaeda founder osama bin laden said: "qutb one affected generation." also described "the source jihadist thought", "the philosopher islamic revolution". 35 years hanged, official commission inquiry al-qaeda's 9/11 attack twin towers 2001 concluded: "bin laden shares qutb's stark view, permitting followers rationalise even unprovoked mass murder righteous defence embattled faith." influence lingers today. summing roots predecessors, iraqi expert islamist movements hisham al-hashemi said: "they founded two things: takfiri faith based writings muhammad ibn abd al-wahhab, me