ismatic dynamic, although join al-qaeda, eventually put charge training camp herat, western afghanistan. worked ideologue whose radical writings became scriptures governing subsequent salafist blood-letting: abu abdullah al-muhajir. "the brutality beheading intended, even delightful god prophet," wrote muhajir book theology jihad, generally referred theology bloodshed. writings provided religious cover brutal excesses, also killing shia infidels, sunni collaborators apostates. book seen virtual manual - even mein kampf - forebears management savagery, abu bakr naji, appeared internet 2004. "we need massacre done banu qurayza, must adopt ruthless policy hostages brutally graphically murdered unless demands met," naji wrote. referring jewish tribe seventh-century arabia reportedly met fate hands early muslims yazidis sinjar nearly 14 centuries later: men slaughtered, women children enslaved. naji's sanctioning exemplary brutality part much wider strategy prepare way islamic caliphate. based partly lessons afghanistan, book detailed blueprint provoking west interventions would rally muslims jihad, leading ultimate collapse enemy. scenario fanciful consider soviet union went pieces barely two years withdrawal afghanistan. naji reported killed us drone strike pakistan's waziristan province 2008. iraq fiasco fallout 9/11 attacks changed things radically jihadists late 2001. us allies bombed invaded afghanistan, ousting taliban, launching wider "war terror" al-qaeda. bin laden went underground, zarqawi others fled. dispersing militants, fired up, badly needed another battlefield provoke confront western enemies. luck side. americans allies long providing it. invasion iraq spring 2003 was, turned out, entirely unjustified chosen grounds - saddam hussein's alleged production weapons mass destruction, supposed support international terrorists, neither true. breaking every state security structure sending thousands disgruntled sunni soldiers officials home, created precisely s