په برتانيا کې دننه او دباندې د بي بي سي د وېبپاڼو ليدنه او کارونه په دې شرايطو کيږي : د بي بي سي وېبپاڼو په کارولو تاسو منلې چې درو شرايطو ته غاړه ږدئ چې په لومړي ځل زموږ ويبپاڼې ته په راتلو عملي کيږي. که چيرې تاسو دغه شرايط نه منئ نو لطفآ د بي بي سي وېبپاڼو ته مه راځئ ، مه يې کاروئ او يا مطالب مه ورته راليږئ. بي بي سي وخت نا وخته دغه شرايط بدلولى شي نو بايد تاسو دغه شرايط تل وگورئ . ستاسو له خوا په پرله پسې توگه د بي بي سي د ويبپاڼو کارول په دې مانا بلل کيږي چې تاسو زموږ له نويو شرايطو سره جوړ ياست . که چيرې تاسو له نويو شرايطو سره نه ياست جوړ نو بايد د وېبپاڼې له کارولو لاس واخلئ . که چيرې د دغو شرايطو او يا د نورو ځانگړو محلي شرايطو چې د بي بي سي په نورو ويبپاڼو کې ليدل کيږي، ترمنځ توپير وي نو وروستۍ بڼه يې پر ځاى ده بي بي سي د ويبپاڼو د کارولو لپاره د نورو شرايطو د لوستلو په نيت دا ځاى کېکاږئ چې په انگليسي ژبه يې ولولئ
people living northern iraq voted overwhelmingly favour independence kurdistan region monday's controversial referendum. electoral commission said 92% 3.3 million kurds non-kurds cast ballots supported secession. announcement came despite last-minute appeal result "cancelled" iraq's prime minister. haider al-abadi urged kurds instead engage dialogue baghdad "in framework constitution". kurdish leaders say "yes" vote give mandate start negotiations secession central government baghdad neighbouring countries. iraq's parliament meanwhile asked prime minister deploy troops oil-rich region kirkuk disputed areas held kurdish forces. kurdish peshmerga fighters took control kirkuk, multi-ethnic region claimed kurds arab-led central government, jihadist militants so-called islamic state (is) swept across northern iraq 2014 iraqi army collapsed. referendum held three iraqi provinces make kurdistan region, well "areas kurdistan outside region's administration". electoral commission officials told news conference irbil wednesday afternoon 2,861,000 people voted "yes" independence 224,000 voted "no". turnout 72.61% among eligible vote. speech parliament result announced, mr abadi insisted would "never dialogue" referendum's outcome kurdistan regional government (krg). vote vehemently opposed baghdad much international community, expressed concern potentially destabilising effects, particularly battle is. mr abadi said priority "preserve citizens' security" promised "defend kurdish citizens inside outside" kurdistan region. "we impose iraq's rule districts region force constitution," added. prime minister also reaffirmed threat prevent direct international flights kurdistan region baghdad given control irbil sulaimaniya airports friday afternoon. krg's transport minister said seeking clarification baghdad. "we don't understand give two airports," mowlud murad told reporters. "they already subject iraqi civil aviation authority." united states, "deeply disappointed" referendum hel