british team developing car capable reaching 1,000mph (1,610km/h). powered rocket bolted eurofighter-typhoon jet engine, vehicle first mount assault world land speed record (763mph; 1,228km/h). bloodhound start running hakskeen pan northern cape, south africa, 2017. it's interesting start new year, various bits car tested slowly get bloodhound ssc ready run. we've still got long way go, it's terrific see systems assembled final installation advanced straight-line racing car ever. last month, small number team went newquay aerohub test jet engine's fuel system (you watch latest bhtv video test here). sounds like easy task - surely need check pump fuel rolls-royce ej200 jet engine quickly enough? unfortunately, it's simple check lot maximum flow rate. example, fuel pumped engine 2g acceleration. throttle back 1,000mph, car slow 3g, want keep engine running help cool car comes stop. heat management going significant part getting 1,000mph safely (i'll talk another time). part problem jet engines create lot heat: "turbine inlet temperature" inside jet 1,500c full power (hotter molten lava volcano). jet engine sits directly base fin (with name it? not, click here). fin aluminium, want avoid excess heat, could weaken structure. giving jet engine couple minutes cool idle power, supersonic run, help control heat build-up rear car. replicate effects g fuel test, team built rig tilt whole fuel system 60 degrees nose-up (to simulate 2g acceleration) 70 degrees nose (simulating 3g deceleration). loads, fuel pumped main fuel tank high-volume aircraft pump (rescued scrap ex-raf tornado). pump runs three-phase alternating current (ac) generated ej200's "aircraft mounted accessory drive", amad (more later). main fuel tank (400 litres) constantly "topped up" two auxiliary tanks (100 litres each) engine start, main tank still full let brakes minutes start. transfer pumps smaller main ac pump (they come scrap tornado) run direct current (dc) car's 24v dc power system. need test main tank ac pump dc transfer pumps. there's more. ej200 high-performance jet engine (it's one things makes raf's typhoon aircraft world-beater), full power still uses fair bit fuel. can't tell exactly much, rolls-royce doesn't publish kind information, wikipedia suggests figure 47 grammes/kilo-newton/second. figure fairly useless, let's develop bit. takes 47g fuel produce one kn thrust one second, max power 90kn, jet use 90 x 47g (=4,230g, 4.23kg) fuel per second. jet fuel 80% density water, 4.23kg equals 5.3 litres fuel per second full power - that's enough empty standard household bucket 2 seconds. like said, it's quite lot fuel. fortunately, bloodhound get standing start 1,000 mph less 1 minute, 400 litres main tank enough get job done. problem pumping five litres/second fuel tank you've got replace something, otherwise tank collapses. fuel tank air vent, allows air tank replace fuel. vent system needs work high acceleration deceleration, leak! finally, world land speed record requires two runs opposite directions within one hour. difficult achieve, provided design car turn-round servicing fairly quickly runs. includes quick refuel (ideally less 10 minutes), need check well. test programme, replaced one access panels clear plastic window, found fascinating. i've lucky enough spend career flying supersonic jet fighters, i've never seen fuel tanks before. watch tank filling short video clip. fuel system get on? overall, really well. small changes make system reliable. example, dc transfer pumps slightly powerful expected, producing over-pressure (about half bar) main tank. avoid risk damaging tank time, fit simple return fuel line, balancing pressures. air vent pipe also turned slightly narrow, causing small dip air pressure maximum flow rate. small increase size air breather ensure good air flow (and fuel flow) throughout run. success - fuel system pretty much ready go. need connect jet engine fire up! ok, it's quite simple. cockpit controls need connected tested, ongoing process. also need able spin jet engine get going. jet's "starter motor" high-speed air turbine (a mere 57,700 revs/minute), connects engine's amad gearbox mentioned earlier. write, amad gearbox starter motor connected tested car. well providing jet engine start capability, spinning amad also drives ac generator (the power supply ac fuel pump), dc generator (dc power whole car), hydraulic pump (hydraulic power airbrakes winglets). spinning gearbox may look like much, get test whole lot car systems do, it's exciting moment us. really time jump fire up. can't wait. getting ready run car first time, we're producing series short videos called anatomy car. episode looks different bit bloodhound ssc, starting front working back. first episode is, predictably, called nose, numbers video quite surprising. maximum speed, aerodynamic load peaks calculated 138,000 pascals (= newtons/sq metre). that's equivalent load two fully-grown elephants… that's nose cone. still, structure strong, i'm worried this. i'm concerned calculated figure aerodynamic heating, suggests possible maximum 134c - would soften carbon fibre nose cone - sitting two large elephants. reality, nose get anywhere near temperature, conduction structure, convection air, remove lot heat (i hope). suspect anatomy car likely show lot big (and possibly scary) numbers works back along car. it's easy see need 500 data sensors car that's hoping travel 1,000mph. bloodhound education team still working hard share excitement 1,000mph "engineering adventure" largest possible audience. great time last week bett show london, telling huge number young people car, letting go rocket cars part "race line" campaign. clearly impact, students voted bloodhound best stand show. well done education team. it's winter uk, it's height summer south africa, also peak rainy season northern cape (they get convective rain - thunderstorms, etc. - summer virtually rain winter). delighted see lot rain falling around hakskeen pan track last mon