2 election mr kibaki reneged pre-election power-sharing deal. astute politician avid campaigner known move crowds using parables football commentary, mr odinga represented lang'ata constituency capital, nairobi, uninterrupted 20 years. refused accept lost 8 august uhuru kenyatta, man beat 2013 election son kenya's first president, jomo kenyatta. mr odinga's father, jaramogi oginga odinga, served jomo kenyatta's vice-president pair fell mr odinga quit 1966, sparking political rivalry yet settled.

